# Frontend and UX rules

## UI/UX direction
- Premium Japanese minimalism.
- Calm, motivating, habit-forming, but no dark patterns.
- Make study feel achievable, especially for busy learners in Japan.
- Support daily-life learning from weather, news, calendar, phrases, and situations.

## i18n
- UI language must support at least Vietnamese and Japanese from the start.
- Do not hard-code visible text in components.
- Use i18n keys and locale files.
- Design for future English or other languages.

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML.
- Keyboard navigation must work for core flows.
- Provide visible focus states.
- Respect reduced motion where animation exists.
- Furigana/romaji toggles should be supported where specified.
